{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[oistre]], [[uistre]] (modern [[huître]]), from Latin [[ostrea]], from Greek [[όστρεον]] (related to [[οστέον]] ‘bone’, [[όστρακον]] ‘shell’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈɔɪstə/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪstə(r)|-ɔɪstə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#Any marine bivalve [[mollusk]] of the Family ''Ostrea'', usually found adhering to rocks or other fixed objects in shallow water along the seacoasts, or in brackish water in the mouth of rivers.
#A name popularly given to the delicate morsel contained in a small cavity of the bone on each side of the lower part of the back of a fowl.
#(colour) a pale beige colour tinted with grey or pink, like that of an oyster.
